document_data.History:
''Circa'' the 14{{th}} century [[DR]], gladiatorial arenas could be found in the [[Moonsea]] city of [[Hillsfar]];<ref name=Moonsea"> [[Calimshan]] in the [[Lands of Intrigue]], the city-state of [[Reth]] in the [[Vilhon Reach]], various locales the [[Dragon Coast]] and perhaps most famously, all across the unforgiving realm of [[Thay]] in the [[Unapproachable East]]. 

[[Tharchion]]s of Thay employed gladiators from many different races, along with monstrous beasts and other fantastic creatures. Due to their size and strength [[goliath]]s made perfect gladiators. Slavers were known to steal goliath infants and raise them as brutal fighters for the arena.{{Cite_dragon/386/Winning_Races:_Goliath_Giants_of_War}}

While gladiatorial contests were forbidden in many other civilized lands during the late 15{{th}} century, as of [[1479 DR]] they remained popular in [[Calimport]], where the [[Pasha]] [[Marod el Arhapan]] held a large number of games in a floating arena. The frontier merchant-city of [[Port Nyanzaru]] in [[Chult]] also maintained a dedicated arena around that time, and small-scale underground fighting pits were not unheard of, such as that found within
the [[Black Blade and Bloody Boar]] in [[Mulmaster]].{{Cite adventurers league/Mayhem in the Earthspur Mines|8}}
